WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:03.136
You're a liability.
You just run off.

2
00:00:03.160 --> 00:00:04.376
do your own thing
at every opportunity.

3
00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:06.416
Have you got ANY idea
how that looks?

4
00:00:06.440 --> 00:00:09.016
We're a man down.
I need someone I can trust.

5
00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:11.296
And I would like you
to act up as DI.

6
00:00:11.320 --> 00:00:14.376
You deliberately misled
me and this team.

7
00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:17.216
-I had no choice.
-No. you had a choice. OK?

8
00:00:17.240 --> 00:00:19.336
You chose the wrong one. Repeatedly.

9
00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:22.056
You could be looking at
a custodial sentence for this. Jay.

10
00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:24.896
Someone will be in touch
about your disciplinary hearing

11
00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:26.136
once the investigation's over.

12
00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:28.056
You should've come to me. Jay.

13
00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:30.400
and I'm sorry that you felt
that you couldn't.

14
00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:38.640
- BAY CITY ROLLERS:
- ♪ If you hate me after what I say

15
00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:42.280
♪ I can't put it off any longer

16
00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:50.440
♪ Just gotta tell her. anyway

17
00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:54.416
♪ Bye-bye. baby
Baby. bye-bye... ♪

18
00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:57.416
One of my favourites. this.

19
00:00:57.440 --> 00:01:00.800
This reminds me of when I used
to go dancing with your dad.

20
00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.256
Grandad. Nana.

21
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:08.056
-What?
-Oh. er... Er. nothing. Never mind. eh?

22
00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:09.576
Oh. was I being daft again?

23
00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:12.736
No. no. no. Happy birthday.

24
00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:14.216
You having a bit of cake. son?

25
00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:16.160
-Eh. aye. yeah. Later.
-Smile!

26
00:01:17.520 --> 00:01:19.397
CAMERA CLICKS

27
00:01:19.421 --> 00:01:21.320
-Yous are adorable!
-I know.

28
00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:28.016
Right. a wee selfie.

29
00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:29.800
CAMERA CLICKS

30
00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:35.656
-What are you wearing?
-Keep them rolls coming. Gemma.

31
00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:37.960
I'm on it. You just
deal with the meat.

32
00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:42.056
Is that venison. Jackson?
Pushing the boat out.

33
00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:45.296
Nah. nothing to do with me.
Gift from His Lordship.

34
00:01:45.320 --> 00:01:48.616
-Ah!
-I hope you're not jumping the queue. Mr Nichols.

35
00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:50.536
Wouldn't dream of it.

36
00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:52.456
-What are you having. wee man?
-Burger. thanks.

37
00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:55.080
Ah. can't go wrong with a burger.

38
00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:57.400
Here you go. mate.

39
00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:00.856
-Oh. Mammy!
-You look great.

40
00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:02.600
THEY LAUGH

41
00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:06.400
-You having one. guys?
-Eh. nah. you're all right.

42
00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:12.776
-Matty. I've. er. I've got a card for your gran.
-Oh. that's nice of you.

43
00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:15.976
Oh. it was nice of her
to invite us. Wasn't it. love?

44
00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.856
Hmm?

45
00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:21.056
-Aye. great.
-Try not to sound too thrilled. Carl.

46
00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.160
-Leese. don't be like that.
-Well...

47
00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:27.056
-What is her problem?
-I don't... I don't know.

48
00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:28.536
I don't know.

49
00:02:28.560 --> 00:02:31.120
-He's still your bestie. then. eh?
-You're my bestie.

50
00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.936
Erm. look. I probably won't be
staying much longer. but...

51
00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:38.216
Oh. Well. brilliant.

52
00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:40.456
-Matty! - No. Come on. - What?
-Well. because you said

53
00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:43.136
-you were going to stay here.
-Yeah. well. I'm sure they'll...

54
00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:46.816
Oh. here we goes. look.
This counting as overtime for you?

55
00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:51.840
No. I'm off the clock. actually.
Just enjoying the harmonious vibes.

56
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.056
Aye. right...

57
00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:58.720
Ignore him. He gets grumpy if he's
not shot anything for a few days.

58
00:03:00.400 --> 00:03:04.136
Well. I suppose
I should. um. do my duty.

59
00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:06.960
-Suppose you should.
-Right.

60
00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:12.256
Er. ladies and gentlemen. if I may.

61
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:13.856
Why can't you stay? Look...

62
00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:15.656
Guys. just. er. just a second.

63
00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:19.640
Oi! A'body! Mr Loughty
wants to say a few words.

64
00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:23.936
Thank you. Mr Gifford.
direct as ever.

65
00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:28.416
Um. look. I couldn't let
the evening pass without a toast

66
00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:32.016
to Rose on her birthday.

67
00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:36.616
She is a remarkable woman. She was
a very dear friend to my mother

68
00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:40.216
and. indeed. she is
a very dear friend to all of us.

69
00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:45.416
So please join me
in raising your glasses.

70
00:03:45.440 --> 00:03:48.240
-To Rose.
-ALL: To Rose.

71
00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:53.256
Oh. it's a shame she can't be
with us today. Dickie.

72
00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:55.696
I'm sorry?

73
00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:59.856
Oh. yes. yes. erm... Yes.
she's a little under the weather.

74
00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:02.656
-Yeah. - Oh. dear.
-It's been a long day. hasn't it. eh?

75
00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:05.680
-Mm. -She gets confused.
-Yes.

76
00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:08.856
Hey. Are you ready for some cake?

77
00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:11.776
-I'm not hungry.
-Oh. great. I'm having to starve cos you're sulking.

78
00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:14.040
-I'm not sulking.
-Right...

79
00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:14.040
PHONE CHIMES

80
00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.040
Look. I've got to go. OK?

81
00:04:34.720 --> 00:04:36.936
PHONE CHIMES

82
00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:38.760
PHONE CLICKS

83
00:06:36.440 --> 00:06:39.816
Morning. Monty. Morning. boss.

84
00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:42.216
Still sounds funny. that.
coming from you.

85
00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:43.976
Would you prefer "ma'am"?

86
00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:46.176
Ha... Would you prefer
a smack in the chops?

87
00:06:46.200 --> 00:06:48.016
I'd stick to "boss" if I was you.

88
00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:50.696
Right. if I could have
everybody's attention. please?

89
00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:53.920
Chief Constable Willis has
something he'd like to say.

90
00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.216
In light of the arrest
and subsequent imprisonment

91
00:06:58.240 --> 00:07:01.216
of Inspector Mallick. this team
will be subject to scrutiny

92
00:07:01.240 --> 00:07:05.696
from officers of the Special
Police Investigations Service.

93
00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:07.520
That process begins tomorrow.

94
00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:12.336
SPIS will be conducting interviews
and accessing files

95
00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:16.896
-from all officers.
-We will of course adhere to any requests.

96
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:19.216
And just to be clear.
this will be a far-reaching

97
00:07:19.240 --> 00:07:23.136
investigation into the wider
practices and culture of the team.

98
00:07:23.160 --> 00:07:26.216
-DS Montrose?
-I can get you interviews. statements.

99
00:07:26.240 --> 00:07:29.336
evidence records and court
testimonies dating back five years.

100
00:07:29.360 --> 00:07:32.376
but anything earlier than that
will take longer.

101
00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:35.696
I could ask my father
to send over some school reports.

102
00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:38.496
And that sort of attitude
won't be tolerated during this

103
00:07:38.520 --> 00:07:40.040
investigation. understood?

104
00:07:41.280 --> 00:07:42.776
Sir.

105
00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:44.280
Thank you. DC Lindo.

106
00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:47.736
Will that be all. sir.
or can we get on with our jobs?

107
00:07:47.760 --> 00:07:50.216
PHONE RINGS

108
00:07:50.240 --> 00:07:52.576
Detective Inspector Barlett.

109
00:07:52.600 --> 00:07:55.520
SIREN WAILS

110
00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:30.376
Richard Loughty.
This is my family's estate.

111
00:08:30.400 --> 00:08:32.496
DCI MacMillan. You found the body?

112
00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:35.456
No. no. Twas me that found her.

113
00:08:35.480 --> 00:08:38.680
-Her name's Lisa Sterling.
-Do you know her?

114
00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:43.256
There's a visitors' cafe
up at the house.

115
00:08:43.280 --> 00:08:45.320
She. er. works there. part-time.

116
00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.120
-Oh. steady.
-I'm fine.

117
00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:03.096
She was just a kid.

118
00:09:03.120 --> 00:09:05.096
So much left to live for.

119
00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:11.000
Mm. My question is. did she fall.
jump or... was she pushed?

120
00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:14.496
Hard to tell.

121
00:09:14.520 --> 00:09:18.256
Get Soco to take more photographs
once the body's been moved. OK?

122
00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:19.720
Will do. boss.

123
00:09:20.680 --> 00:09:22.736
Never would have thought of that
myself. obviously.

124
00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:25.960
Hey. you think it's weird he called
his boss before he called us?

125
00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:29.696
No. not necessarily.

126
00:09:29.720 --> 00:09:33.816
The guys that work on these estates.
job for life. goes back generations.

127
00:09:33.840 --> 00:09:35.800
You're talking blind loyalty?

128
00:09:36.760 --> 00:09:38.416
Yeah. maybe.

129
00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:41.096
OK. The house is up this way. so...

130
00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:44.896
-How well did you know Lisa?
-She'd been working here for a few months.

131
00:09:44.920 --> 00:09:49.176
-And I saw her last night at Rose Gough's party.
-Was Rose a friend?

132
00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:52.856
I mean. not a friend.
Like. she's ancient. 75.

133
00:09:52.880 --> 00:09:55.736
But her family are Travellers.
my family are Travellers.

134
00:09:55.760 --> 00:09:58.376
It was her birthday.

135
00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:00.416
But Lisa wasn't a Traveller?

136
00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:03.936
She knocked around with Matty.
Rose's grandson.

137
00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:09.416
-Like boyfriend-girlfriend?
-No idea. She only worked here at busy times.

138
00:10:09.440 --> 00:10:12.536
so I never really
got the chance to ask.

139
00:10:12.560 --> 00:10:15.560
-Everything OK. Gemma?
-OK?

140
00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:19.536
Ah. sorry. Ridiculous question.
given the circumstances.

141
00:10:19.560 --> 00:10:21.816
She's been very helpful.

142
00:10:21.840 --> 00:10:25.016
-I was just telling them about the party last night.
-Oh. right.

143
00:10:25.040 --> 00:10:29.616
-You were there. too?
-Yeah. for a little while. We've always had

144
00:10:29.640 --> 00:10:32.400
very good relationships
with the Traveller community.

145
00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:37.576
-Lady Loughty gave me this job.
-Yeah. so she did.

146
00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:40.776
Do either of you
have Lisa's home address?

147
00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:44.840
Er. it'll be on file
in the office. I expect. This way.

148
00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:56.280
PHONE VIBRATES

149
00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:00.936
DCI MacMillan.

150
00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:03.960
I'm afraid this isn't
a convenient time to talk.

151
00:11:08.120 --> 00:11:11.496
OK. I. er. I appreciate that. yeah.

152
00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:13.680
I'll call you back
as soon as possible.

153
00:11:16.760 --> 00:11:19.920
Time of death
between 10pm and midnight.

154
00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:22.776
Boss?

155
00:11:22.800 --> 00:11:24.216
Ma'am?

156
00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:28.776
-Cause of death?
-It's looking like a broken neck. but that's unconfirmed.

157
00:11:28.800 --> 00:11:31.696
This is the only thing found
on her person. There's no power.

158
00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:34.256
-so I don't know if it's damaged.
-OK. well. get that fired up

159
00:11:34.280 --> 00:11:37.056
-back at the station. That will give us her network. at least.
-Boss.

160
00:11:37.080 --> 00:11:39.776
You liaise with the Socos
so we can get immediate access

161
00:11:39.800 --> 00:11:43.416
to the photos and all the evidence.
I'll get uniform to do a fingertip

162
00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:46.616
search with a radius
of two hundred and f...

163
00:11:46.640 --> 00:11:48.856
Actually. no. make it
three hundred metres.

164
00:11:48.880 --> 00:11:51.336
-That's quite some distance.
-We proceed on the basis that this is

165
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:54.320
-a murder until we know it's an accident.
-Boss.

166
00:12:03.680 --> 00:12:05.360
SHE SIGHS

167
00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:13.536
Did you speak to Lisa at the party?

168
00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:16.856
No. I didn't stay very long.
just showed my face in the name of

169
00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:19.816
-community relations.
-Was Mr Gifford there?

170
00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:22.696
Er. yes. Yes. he was.
as a matter of fact.

171
00:12:22.720 --> 00:12:26.440
-Did you notice anything unusual about Lisa?
-Oh. I barely saw her.

172
00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:33.360
Er. yeah. I. erm. I was tempted
to get rid of this stuff.

173
00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:38.856
It all seemed a tad...
well. colonial.

174
00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:42.776
But. erm. visitors
find it fascinating.

175
00:12:42.800 --> 00:12:45.216
Not the word I would use.

176
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:47.056
No.

177
00:12:47.080 --> 00:12:50.496
My ancestors' experiences
of the colonial past was a tad

178
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:53.320
-different from yours.
-I can imagine. yeah.

179
00:12:55.960 --> 00:12:59.336
-Will you be needing anything else?
-Er. no. not for the time being.

180
00:12:59.360 --> 00:13:02.440
but the entire estate
needs to be closed to visitors.

181
00:13:03.400 --> 00:13:06.816
-Of course.
-And the staff need to steer clear of the spot where

182
00:13:06.840 --> 00:13:11.056
-the body was found.
-Any idea... how long for?

183
00:13:11.080 --> 00:13:14.120
-Until we say otherwise.
-Right.

184
00:13:40.200 --> 00:13:43.360
I love my job. but I hate
this part of it.

185
00:13:54.160 --> 00:13:55.880
Was she...?

186
00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:02.160
Where did you find her?

187
00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:06.200
The woods near Loughty Hall.

188
00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:12.416
-Near the Travellers. you mean?
-I'm not with you.

189
00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:14.320
HE SCOFFS

190
00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:19.776
I get called a bigot for saying
that she should stay away from them.

191
00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:21.616
and now look.

192
00:14:21.640 --> 00:14:24.176
We heard that Lisa was seeing
a Traveller boy. Is that right?

193
00:14:24.200 --> 00:14:25.360
Aye.

194
00:14:26.320 --> 00:14:27.600
Matty.

195
00:14:29.280 --> 00:14:33.016
-They were arguing last night.
-And this was at the party?

196
00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:35.256
-You were there. too?
-Aye.

197
00:14:35.280 --> 00:14:37.936
What was the argument about?

198
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:40.176
Couldn't tell you.

199
00:14:40.200 --> 00:14:41.936
I saw it. but I didnae hear it.

200
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:43.616
What time was this?

201
00:14:43.640 --> 00:14:45.640
About nine?

202
00:14:46.600 --> 00:14:49.256
Ah. about nine.
We were back here for ten. eh?

203
00:14:49.280 --> 00:14:50.880
Janine needs her rest.

204
00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:57.480
And you weren't concerned when
she didn't come home last night?

205
00:14:59.760 --> 00:15:01.440
No. I just...

206
00:15:02.400 --> 00:15:04.400
I thought she'd crashed at Matty's.

207
00:15:06.520 --> 00:15:09.160
-It's him you want to talk to.
-We will.

208
00:15:10.120 --> 00:15:12.960
Would it be possible
to see her room. please?

209
00:15:16.720 --> 00:15:18.080
This Matty?

210
00:15:20.080 --> 00:15:21.880
Aye. Aye. that's him.

211
00:15:22.840 --> 00:15:24.400
Do you mind if we take it?

212
00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:26.720
Whatever you need.

213
00:15:29.240 --> 00:15:33.496
We found Lisa's phone. It would be
really useful if we could access it.

214
00:15:33.520 --> 00:15:36.536
-Have you got any idea what her passcode is?
-Agh...

215
00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:38.736
Not a clue. Sorry.

216
00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:40.640
12-11-19.

217
00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:44.656
Spike's birthday.

218
00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:47.600
We had to give him away
when Carl moved in.

219
00:15:48.560 --> 00:15:50.280
Allergies. y'know.

220
00:15:51.240 --> 00:15:52.856
DOORBELL MOTHER GASPS

221
00:15:52.880 --> 00:15:55.520
That'll be
the family liaison officer.

222
00:15:57.080 --> 00:15:58.680
Aye...

223
00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:06.216
When I heard the door there. I...

224
00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:11.240
I thought. "Oh. that'll be Leese -
forgot her keys again."

225
00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:19.296
There was this. er... one night...

226
00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:20.720
I don't know...

227
00:16:23.560 --> 00:16:24.880
Go on.

228
00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:31.800
One night. Lisa said
that she was out with Matty...

229
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:38.656
and. er. then he turned up here.
said he forgot his charger.

230
00:16:38.680 --> 00:16:40.240
When was this?

231
00:16:42.320 --> 00:16:45.320
Oh. a month. six weeks.
I don't know.

232
00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:49.880
And have you got any idea
who she was actually with?

233
00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:54.960
No. We hadn't been
speaking much lately.

234
00:16:58.760 --> 00:17:00.520
Hey.

235
00:17:15.360 --> 00:17:17.616
Thank you for contacting
the Farrar Centre.

236
00:17:17.640 --> 00:17:20.480
Your call is really important to us.

237
00:17:23.800 --> 00:17:25.237
KNOCK ON DOOR

238
00:17:25.261 --> 00:17:26.696
Come in.

239
00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:30.840
-Oh. I can come back.
-No. no. no. I'm on hold... indefinitely.

240
00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:35.576
It's a murder investigation.
Confirmed.

241
00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:38.456
Lisa Sterling's injuries
are not consistent with a fall.

242
00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:40.856
They're entirely to the neck
and the rear of her skull.

243
00:17:40.880 --> 00:17:43.656
-She was pushed.
-And with considerable force.

244
00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:46.656
Bart gave me the code
to access Lisa's phone.

245
00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:49.136
The last text was from
the boyfriend. Matty -

246
00:17:49.160 --> 00:17:51.216
"Please don't do this."

247
00:17:51.240 --> 00:17:54.496
-Oh. so emotions were running high.
-So it seems.

248
00:17:54.520 --> 00:17:57.096
Bart and Davis are heading out
to talk to him now.

249
00:17:57.120 --> 00:17:59.160
Hi there. caller.
Thanks for holdi...

250
00:18:06.200 --> 00:18:07.896
Ah!

251
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:09.440
OK...

252
00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:15.776
-Hey. man. what's your name?
-I'm Noah.

253
00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:18.416
Noah. Hi. Noah.
We're looking for a young ma...

254
00:18:18.440 --> 00:18:20.896
-He doesn't need to answer your questions.
-We haven't

255
00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:24.136
asked him any yet. We're just
looking for a Matthew Gough.

256
00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:26.656
-Why?
-You know him?

257
00:18:26.680 --> 00:18:29.160
-He's a good kid.
-So he's got nothing to worry about.

258
00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:32.576
Yeah. cos that's how it works...

259
00:18:32.600 --> 00:18:35.720
OK. we just need to go
door-to-door. then.

260
00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:39.240
OK.

261
00:18:40.200 --> 00:18:41.320
OK.

262
00:18:42.360 --> 00:18:43.720
This way.

263
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:51.000
-Drina!
-Yeah? Everything all right?

264
00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:54.896
They want a word with your Matty.

265
00:18:54.920 --> 00:18:57.440
-Drina's his ma.
-Hi. I'm DI Bartlett.

266
00:18:58.600 --> 00:19:01.736
-This is my colleague. DC Lindo.
-Is your son home?

267
00:19:01.760 --> 00:19:04.856
-No. not seen him since last night.
-Have you heard from him?

268
00:19:04.880 --> 00:19:07.416
Not a word. no.
Probably stayed at his pal's.

269
00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:09.296
Can you tell us his pal's name?

270
00:19:09.320 --> 00:19:11.856
Lisa. Lisa Sterling.

271
00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:15.280
-Is that Matty's girlfriend?
-No. No. they're just mates.

272
00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:20.360
What's going on?

273
00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:23.856
Do you mind if we have
a word inside?

274
00:19:23.880 --> 00:19:26.696
-Don't you need a warrant for that?
-Not if Mrs Gough is happy

275
00:19:26.720 --> 00:19:31.080
-to have a conversation.
-All right. come on in.

276
00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:42.456
Drina?

277
00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:46.096
Just... give us a shout
if you need anything.

278
00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:47.480
Aye.

279
00:19:50.560 --> 00:19:53.696
-Who's this?
-Ah. just you finish your tea and take your tablets. Rose.

280
00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:55.720
Nothing to worry about.

281
00:19:56.680 --> 00:19:59.600
-Is there?
-We're just looking to talk to Matty.

282
00:20:00.560 --> 00:20:02.720
Oh. Matty's long dead.

283
00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:07.336
-It's young Matty they're interested in. Rose.
-Oh. right.

284
00:20:07.360 --> 00:20:10.800
Mother-in-law gets a bit confused.
My boy was named after her husband.

285
00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:16.256
Could we see Matty's room?

286
00:20:16.280 --> 00:20:18.640
Aye. It's through there.

287
00:20:36.800 --> 00:20:39.856
These are nice. Neatly kept.

288
00:20:39.880 --> 00:20:42.840
Mm. like they mean a lot to him.

289
00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:47.256
Could you give us
Matty's mobile number?

290
00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:50.456
-It's really important we talk to him.
-OK.

291
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:53.576
But you may as well
just phone Lisa's house.

292
00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:58.240
Mrs Gough. I'm afraid that Lisa
was found dead this morning.

293
00:21:00.080 --> 00:21:01.320
What?

294
00:21:02.960 --> 00:21:04.296
What? No way.

295
00:21:04.320 --> 00:21:05.696
Wait. but how?

296
00:21:05.720 --> 00:21:09.336
That's what
we're trying to find out.

297
00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:13.000
Right. I'll. erm.
I'll go find the number.

298
00:21:16.280 --> 00:21:20.496
Look around. Bart -
the wardrobe. the bed.

299
00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:24.216
the drawers - it's like
someone already searched this place.

300
00:21:24.240 --> 00:21:28.880
-Mm. or wanted to grab something and get out fast.
-Mm.

301
00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:32.840
-Here it is.
-Thanks.

302
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:38.840
-Does Matty have a current passport?
-Er. no. Erm...

303
00:21:40.440 --> 00:21:42.760
Wait. why does that matter?

304
00:21:46.040 --> 00:21:48.600
I mean it! Out!

305
00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:52.456
-What's going on?
-Lisa's dead. and they're after my Matty for it.

306
00:21:52.480 --> 00:21:55.616
-We're just trying to talk to him.
-I don't know where he is.

307
00:21:55.640 --> 00:21:57.456
but he would never
lay a hand on her!

308
00:21:57.480 --> 00:22:00.456
Let's just all try and keep
a calm head. shall we?

309
00:22:00.480 --> 00:22:03.496
Alex Nichols.
Traveller community liaison ACC.

310
00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:07.016
-DI Bartlett. - DC Lindo.
-We're trying to establish what happened.

311
00:22:07.040 --> 00:22:08.816
And then blame it
on the nearest Traveller. yeah?

312
00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:11.376
-That's not how we operate.
-Been that way in the past.

313
00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:13.480
Not from me. not from us. OK?

314
00:22:18.600 --> 00:22:21.136
Look. you need to understand
the level of prejudice

315
00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:24.016
-they experience as a community.
-Yeah. we understand. We're not

316
00:22:24.040 --> 00:22:27.336
-jumping to any conclusions.
-But we do need to speak to Matty.

317
00:22:27.360 --> 00:22:30.680
-Erm. try the college in town. He's studying sports science there.
-OK.

318
00:22:31.640 --> 00:22:34.456
-Were you at Rose Gough's party last night?
-Yeah. I was.

319
00:22:34.480 --> 00:22:37.816
If you took any pictures. videos.
posted anything on social media.

320
00:22:37.840 --> 00:22:40.496
if you could forward it to us.
that would be great.

321
00:22:40.520 --> 00:22:43.056
Get the others to do the same.
It's better coming from you.

322
00:22:43.080 --> 00:22:45.736
-Yeah. definitely.
-Thanks.

323
00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:50.936
-Oh. er. try Mr Marsh. He helped Matty out a while back.
-Helped how?

324
00:22:50.960 --> 00:22:53.616
Yeah. he got in a bit of bother. He
got in a fight with another student.

325
00:22:53.640 --> 00:22:55.240
OK. Thanks.

326
00:23:04.120 --> 00:23:06.576
Look. it's all going to be fine.
guys. nothing to worry about.

327
00:23:06.600 --> 00:23:09.240
-They're just doing their usual inquiries.
-Are they coming back?

328
00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:15.480
It's. er...

329
00:23:16.440 --> 00:23:19.496
Agh. it's such a shock.

330
00:23:19.520 --> 00:23:22.056
Should the school be
making some form of...

331
00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:23.736
official announcement here. or...?

332
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:26.200
Maybe hold off
till the end of the day.

333
00:23:27.160 --> 00:23:30.256
Did Matty have any pals
that he might go to

334
00:23:30.280 --> 00:23:31.880
if he was worried or in trouble?

335
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:36.136
Not really. I only ever
saw him with Lisa.

336
00:23:36.160 --> 00:23:38.536
Is this her locker?

337
00:23:38.560 --> 00:23:41.816
Good Lord! Er. yeah. Yes. it is.

338
00:23:41.840 --> 00:23:43.360
Is that recent?

339
00:23:44.640 --> 00:23:49.216
Of course. The janitor wouldn't
leave something like that up.

340
00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:51.896
Look. this is a safe space
for our students.

341
00:23:51.920 --> 00:23:54.816
But you did keep
Matty Gough around after

342
00:23:54.840 --> 00:23:56.720
he was involved in
a violent incident.

343
00:23:58.040 --> 00:24:02.256
-Yeah. I thought he deserved a second chance.
-Who was he fighting?

344
00:24:02.280 --> 00:24:05.280
-Adam. Er. Adam Colgan.
-What was it about?

345
00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.720
I'm not sure. actually.

346
00:24:09.680 --> 00:24:11.976
You can ask him yourself.
if you like.

347
00:24:12.000 --> 00:24:13.760
Adam!

348
00:24:15.520 --> 00:24:17.400
-Adam!
-Hey!

349
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:30.640
Hey!

350
00:24:33.920 --> 00:24:38.320
-Don't move.
-OK. Adam. what's in the bag?

351
00:24:41.200 --> 00:24:46.656
-Oh! Hello!
-That made you give it the full Usain Bolt?

352
00:24:46.680 --> 00:24:49.496
-I panicked a bit.
-How did you even know we were police?

353
00:24:49.520 --> 00:24:52.296
You talked to Marshy.
It all looked a bit official.

354
00:24:52.320 --> 00:24:54.496
Yeah. Marshy told us about
your fight with Matty Gough.

355
00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:57.616
-It wasnae a fight. it was a sucker punch.
-Why would he do that?

356
00:24:57.640 --> 00:25:00.136
-Ask him.
-I'm asking you.

357
00:25:00.160 --> 00:25:03.336
He was sniffing about my ex.
made a joke about her.

358
00:25:03.360 --> 00:25:05.816
Next thing I know. he jumps me.

359
00:25:05.840 --> 00:25:07.720
Was your ex Lisa Sterling?

360
00:25:08.680 --> 00:25:10.336
How do you know that?

361
00:25:10.360 --> 00:25:12.616
What was you doing last night
from 10pm onwards?

362
00:25:12.640 --> 00:25:14.920
-Is this serious. then. yeah?
-Answer the question.

363
00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:18.136
-I was at home. gaming.
-Do you live with your parents?

364
00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:21.576
-My mum. yeah. but she was working.
-Have you seen Matty Gough today?

365
00:25:21.600 --> 00:25:25.080
Nah. Why. what's going on?
Is Lisa OK?

366
00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:33.520
-Come on. -Up!
-Jesus!

367
00:25:34.480 --> 00:25:39.160
Hi. Please. son. call me
as soon as you get this.

368
00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:41.576
Look. whatever you've...

369
00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:43.776
Whatever's happened. just...

370
00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:46.320
I love you. all right?
And I want to help.

371
00:25:47.280 --> 00:25:48.840
Please.

372
00:26:06.880 --> 00:26:09.416
Productive shift. DI Bartlett?

373
00:26:09.440 --> 00:26:14.856
Erm. frustrating. to be honest. sir.
Can't locate the victim's boyfriend.

374
00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:17.776
Photograph distributed to airlines
and ferry terminals?

375
00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:20.936
-Yeah. he doesn't have a passport.
-He can't have gone too far. then.

376
00:26:20.960 --> 00:26:23.496
I understand this will be
a difficult week. with SPIS

377
00:26:23.520 --> 00:26:26.736
arriving in the midst
of a murder investigation.

378
00:26:26.760 --> 00:26:29.456
I mean. it's not ideal. sir. no.

379
00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:32.096
Well. you should take some comfort
in the fact that you're very highly

380
00:26:32.120 --> 00:26:35.016
thought of within the department.
and the fact that you were a junior

381
00:26:35.040 --> 00:26:38.056
officer during this whole Mallick
fiasco means it's highly unlikely

382
00:26:38.080 --> 00:26:42.016
that you'll be expected to shoulder
any significant responsibility.

383
00:26:42.040 --> 00:26:46.880
-Right...
-To put it simply. SPIS have got bigger fish to fry.

384
00:26:48.480 --> 00:26:50.400
Have a good evening.

385
00:26:54.320 --> 00:26:56.000
I could do with a drink.

386
00:26:56.960 --> 00:26:59.680
Yeah. Yeah. me too.

387
00:27:03.840 --> 00:27:06.536
-What was the high heid yin after?
-SHE LAUGHS.

388
00:27:06.560 --> 00:27:10.496
-What?
-Still working your way through that Scottish dictionary. I see.

389
00:27:10.520 --> 00:27:12.480
Best secret Santa ever!

390
00:27:13.440 --> 00:27:15.336
Willis just wanted updating.

391
00:27:15.360 --> 00:27:17.656
I told him what we've got.
which isn't much.

392
00:27:17.680 --> 00:27:20.160
It's funny he didn't go to Mac.
I don't think he's a fan.

393
00:27:21.560 --> 00:27:25.240
Or maybe he just thinks
that I'm a competent professional.

394
00:27:26.320 --> 00:27:29.176
Excuse me. it's DI Bartlett. yeah?

395
00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:32.736
-Yes...?
-Harper Ross. We met at the Women In Policing event

396
00:27:32.760 --> 00:27:35.736
-a couple of years ago. You gave a cool speech.
-Yeah. Yeah. course.

397
00:27:35.760 --> 00:27:38.776
-How you doing?
-Thirsty. Can I get you a drink?

398
00:27:38.800 --> 00:27:42.056
Ah. Erm. I was just leaving.

399
00:27:42.080 --> 00:27:45.000
-Sorry.
-No biggie.

400
00:27:47.160 --> 00:27:49.400
-Was it something I said?
-No. no. that's all on me.

401
00:27:50.840 --> 00:27:54.176
-In that case. you need to stay.
-Because?

402
00:27:54.200 --> 00:27:56.496
Because otherwise
I'd be drinking alone.

403
00:27:56.520 --> 00:27:59.776
-I can see your friends are over there.
-They're just finishing up.

404
00:27:59.800 --> 00:28:02.656
I thought I'd stick around.
I knew I'd seen a familiar face.

405
00:28:02.680 --> 00:28:06.896
and I did. and then she left
because of you.

406
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:10.736
OK. OK. I'll have a drink.
Same again. please. And...?

407
00:28:10.760 --> 00:28:14.776
-G&T.
-So. you're a copper. then?

408
00:28:14.800 --> 00:28:17.296
-Used to be.
-Why did you quit?

409
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.016
I get that there's a glass ceiling.

410
00:28:19.040 --> 00:28:22.216
but I was so many floors below
I couldn't even see it.

411
00:28:22.240 --> 00:28:24.136
Mm. that's a shame.

412
00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:27.536
Starting a new gig next month.
though. so. y'know. their loss.

413
00:28:27.560 --> 00:28:29.816
You're not afraid of
bigging up yourself. then?

414
00:28:29.840 --> 00:28:32.336
-I'm not afraid of anything.
-Oh. yeah?

415
00:28:32.360 --> 00:28:35.296
I've got a healthy ego. Pretty sure
you can relate with that.

416
00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:37.056
So you're analysing me?

417
00:28:37.080 --> 00:28:40.880
Let's just say that's not the shirt
and tie combo of an insecure man.

418
00:28:43.920 --> 00:28:45.440
Chin-chin.

419
00:29:08.600 --> 00:29:10.440
ENGINE STARTS

420
00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:18.920
TYRES SQUEAL

421
00:29:21.800 --> 00:29:25.256
-Where do you live? -Sorry?
-I've got a cab coming.

422
00:29:25.280 --> 00:29:27.976
-We could split it?
-Milligan Street.

423
00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:29.576
I'm on the other side of town.

424
00:29:29.600 --> 00:29:31.896
Pity. we could have talked more
on the way.

425
00:29:31.920 --> 00:29:35.536
Yeah. I've enjoyed our conversation
so far. Harper.

426
00:29:35.560 --> 00:29:37.280
Me too. Davis.

427
00:29:39.000 --> 00:29:40.480
CAR PULLS UP

428
00:29:43.920 --> 00:29:46.080
How chivalrous.

429
00:29:47.560 --> 00:29:51.520
You want to... continue
the conversation. then?

430
00:30:17.840 --> 00:30:20.936
Same suit two days on the run?
That's not like you.

431
00:30:20.960 --> 00:30:24.360
-The dry-cleaner's let me down.
-They do your ties as well?

432
00:30:28.320 --> 00:30:32.056
-Are you getting anywhere yet?
-Er. the investigation's ongoing.

433
00:30:32.080 --> 00:30:35.096
Janine has just identified
her daughter's body.

434
00:30:35.120 --> 00:30:38.560
-Now. we have a right to know what's happening.
-Of course.

435
00:30:39.880 --> 00:30:43.256
-Have you spoken to Matty?
-We've not been able to locate him.

436
00:30:43.280 --> 00:30:46.296
-Seriously?
-When we speak to him. we'll know more.

437
00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:49.896
What else is there to know?
If he's done a runner. it looks bad.

438
00:30:49.920 --> 00:30:53.536
-But isn't it always the boyfriend?
-Not necessarily.

439
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:57.856
You're no' tiptoeing about the
Travellers. are you? Not being woke?

440
00:30:57.880 --> 00:31:00.776
Questioning Matthew Gough
is our number one priority.

441
00:31:00.800 --> 00:31:04.320
-Carl. just let them do their jobs. eh?
-Aye.

442
00:31:06.080 --> 00:31:08.200
How did you get on
with your stepdaughter?

443
00:31:09.840 --> 00:31:11.640
-Who. me?
-You.

444
00:31:13.320 --> 00:31:15.616
Well. I'm married to her mum.
we're having a baby.

445
00:31:15.640 --> 00:31:17.720
Sure. we had our run-ins.

446
00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:22.576
Hold on. you're not accusing me
of anything here. are you?

447
00:31:22.600 --> 00:31:24.936
Nobody is accusing you of anything.

448
00:31:24.960 --> 00:31:27.040
-All right. good.
-Come on.

449
00:31:30.600 --> 00:31:32.136
What are you rattling his cage for?

450
00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:34.680
Because it's not always
the boyfriend.

451
00:31:46.640 --> 00:31:49.536
Lisa's phone has given us
an insight into her life.

452
00:31:49.560 --> 00:31:52.536
We've got her social media.
emails. texts.

453
00:31:52.560 --> 00:31:54.576
and photos from Rose Gough's party.

454
00:31:54.600 --> 00:31:57.736
We told the Traveller liaison guy
to ask the rest of the community.

455
00:31:57.760 --> 00:32:00.736
Yeah. they're already starting
to come in. I'm working my way

456
00:32:00.760 --> 00:32:03.560
through them. but for the moment
I wanted you to see this.

457
00:32:04.560 --> 00:32:07.936
There are multiple abusive comments
here from different user names.

458
00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:10.736
but they all read like they're
from the same person somehow.

459
00:32:10.760 --> 00:32:14.096
"Nasty Maggot." "Tramp GOAT."
"Desperate Skank."

460
00:32:14.120 --> 00:32:17.536
-It's targeted abuse. like a fixation.
-It could be a pile-on.

461
00:32:17.560 --> 00:32:21.856
-Could be stalker behaviour.
-So Matty repeatedly calls the troll out.

462
00:32:21.880 --> 00:32:24.416
using aggressive language
of his own.

463
00:32:24.440 --> 00:32:29.176
Well. that's a pattern. He got into
a fight with someone at college

464
00:32:29.200 --> 00:32:32.696
over Lisa. he's threatening
someone online over Lisa.

465
00:32:32.720 --> 00:32:35.176
he's treating those postcards
like love letters.

466
00:32:35.200 --> 00:32:36.976
I wouldn't go that far.

467
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:39.560
Feels borderline obsessive to me.

468
00:32:40.960 --> 00:32:45.016
Er. right. Monty. try and find out
if the accounts posting the abusive

469
00:32:45.040 --> 00:32:48.136
comments are from the same VPN.

470
00:32:48.160 --> 00:32:51.616
And if they are. then get a warrant
for the right IP address.

471
00:32:51.640 --> 00:32:56.080
Can you just bring me up the footage
of Lisa that you showed me earlier?

472
00:33:01.760 --> 00:33:03.976
This is late on at the party.

473
00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:06.056
This is Lisa heading into the woods.

474
00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:09.520
-And... this is Matty.
-They're not leaving together.

475
00:33:11.880 --> 00:33:14.776
It's like he's following her.

476
00:33:14.800 --> 00:33:19.816
So. as this footage was being taken.
Matty sent Lisa a text.

477
00:33:19.840 --> 00:33:23.696
"Please don't do this."
No emoji. no kisses.

478
00:33:23.720 --> 00:33:27.136
-He's imploring her.
-Does that make the boy a murderer?

479
00:33:27.160 --> 00:33:29.336
Makes him our prime suspect.

480
00:33:29.360 --> 00:33:30.880
Agreed.

481
00:33:31.840 --> 00:33:36.216
Please forgive the interruptions.
The SPIS team have arrived.

482
00:33:36.240 --> 00:33:39.320
-I'll leave you to make your own introductions.
-Sir.

483
00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:42.936
Play nice.

484
00:33:42.960 --> 00:33:45.096
That's her from the pub last night.

485
00:33:45.120 --> 00:33:48.376
DI Bartlett. DC Lindo.
you're free to go and do your work.

486
00:33:48.400 --> 00:33:53.936
See if you can find Matty Gough's
phone or. better still. Matty Gough.

487
00:33:53.960 --> 00:33:55.936
-Ma'am.
-Got it. boss.

488
00:33:55.960 --> 00:33:58.000
-Just give me a second. yeah?
-Yeah.

489
00:34:12.520 --> 00:34:15.336
-What game are you playing. Harper?
-There's no games involved.

490
00:34:15.360 --> 00:34:18.216
-I shouldn't even be here.
-You got that right.

491
00:34:18.240 --> 00:34:23.016
I'm supposed to start with SPIS
next month - maternity leave cover -

492
00:34:23.040 --> 00:34:26.016
but the woman went into labour
last night. three weeks early.

493
00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:27.376
otherwise she'd be on this.

494
00:34:27.400 --> 00:34:29.600
You never mentioned that at all
last night.

495
00:34:30.560 --> 00:34:33.840
-Well. it's a bit of a passion killer.
-Yeah...

496
00:34:34.800 --> 00:34:38.160
If I say anything now. I'll lose
the gig and I won't get it back.

497
00:34:39.400 --> 00:34:41.776
That's a big price to pay
for one night.

498
00:34:41.800 --> 00:34:43.776
So you've decided
it's only one night?

499
00:34:43.800 --> 00:34:46.696
Well. you didn't stick around
for breakfast. did you?

500
00:34:46.720 --> 00:34:49.016
Davis. do not scupper this for me.

501
00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:51.920
Lindo. let's go.
Matty's used his phone.

502
00:35:15.680 --> 00:35:18.016
The phone was only on
for a couple of seconds.

503
00:35:18.040 --> 00:35:21.120
-Close to where we found Lisa?
-Close enough.

504
00:35:33.880 --> 00:35:35.936
The network can't give us
a precise location.

505
00:35:35.960 --> 00:35:38.576
but it was definitely
in these woods.

506
00:35:38.600 --> 00:35:40.520
PHONE VIBRATES

507
00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:46.656
Whoa. whoa. whoa. This is bad.

508
00:35:46.680 --> 00:35:47.936
What is?

509
00:35:47.960 --> 00:35:50.680
Monty found this on Lisa's socials.

510
00:35:51.800 --> 00:35:53.480
SHE GROANS

511
00:35:58.480 --> 00:36:00.856
We know these things
can escalate quickly.

512
00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:04.296
but I'm going to be around
and I've got your backs.

513
00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:07.016
I will liaise with the police
as and when. and I'm pushing the

514
00:36:07.040 --> 00:36:11.376
social media companies to take down
the comments on hate speech grounds.

515
00:36:11.400 --> 00:36:15.136
But for now. just try and keep calm
and keep your heads down.

516
00:36:15.160 --> 00:36:18.096
-When do we ever do any different?
-Well. you know what I mean.

517
00:36:18.120 --> 00:36:20.480
I'm here to look out for
your best int...

518
00:36:25.960 --> 00:36:28.816
-What?
-Look. I don't think you being here is...

519
00:36:28.840 --> 00:36:30.920
I don't give a toss what
you've got to say. mate. eh?

520
00:36:31.880 --> 00:36:33.600
I need to speak to Drina.

521
00:36:34.600 --> 00:36:36.320
Aye. Come on in.

522
00:36:37.560 --> 00:36:39.320
Just the two of us.

523
00:36:40.760 --> 00:36:42.560
Thanks.

524
00:36:56.520 --> 00:36:59.576
This could end in
a vigilante mob situation.

525
00:36:59.600 --> 00:37:02.880
-Yeah. All the more reason to find him before someone else does.
-Mm.

526
00:37:06.480 --> 00:37:07.656
CRACK

527
00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:09.960
-What was that?
-What?

528
00:37:15.600 --> 00:37:17.256
What are you doing here. sir?

529
00:37:17.280 --> 00:37:22.696
-Part of the estate. I'm always here.
-Have you seen Matty Gough?

530
00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:25.360
Has there been any movement
around here today?

531
00:37:26.640 --> 00:37:31.176
-Nope.
-Are there any places to take shelter? Like a cave? A shed?

532
00:37:31.200 --> 00:37:33.280
Somewhere to build a den?

533
00:37:34.240 --> 00:37:36.240
Probably half a dozen.

534
00:37:37.200 --> 00:37:39.000
Start with the one closest to here.

535
00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:42.416
Now would be great.

536
00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:44.317
HE SIGHS

537
00:37:44.341 --> 00:37:46.240
Right. follow me.

538
00:37:51.080 --> 00:37:52.400
Look...

539
00:37:53.360 --> 00:37:56.456
I know that this is
hard for you to hear.

540
00:37:56.480 --> 00:38:00.000
But believe me.
it's harder for me to say.

541
00:38:01.800 --> 00:38:03.480
Yeah. I understand.

542
00:38:07.760 --> 00:38:09.840
Mother to mother...

543
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:13.416
please tell me the truth.

544
00:38:13.440 --> 00:38:15.896
Did Matty do it?

545
00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:18.016
Did he kill my Lisa?

546
00:38:18.040 --> 00:38:22.136
I know. I know in my heart of hearts
that he would never.

547
00:38:22.160 --> 00:38:26.456
-never do anything to harm that girl.
-Drina... -He loved her.

548
00:38:26.480 --> 00:38:29.880
Then where is he?! Tell me that!

549
00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:35.800
-You OK. love? I could hear shouting.
-Yeah. don't worry.

550
00:38:37.840 --> 00:38:41.096
-Are you hiding him somewhere here?
-Get out of my home. -Answer me!

551
00:38:41.120 --> 00:38:42.720
Carl. leave it.

552
00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:46.840
Well. somebody has got to
do something!

553
00:39:01.000 --> 00:39:04.040
-Where is this den?
-It's just up ahead.

554
00:39:07.360 --> 00:39:09.520
You should wait here. sir.

555
00:39:10.480 --> 00:39:13.296
You really think
the Gough boy's dangerous?

556
00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:15.160
Better safe than sorry.

557
00:39:17.400 --> 00:39:19.400
Lindo...

558
00:39:20.360 --> 00:39:22.616
That blood?

559
00:39:22.640 --> 00:39:24.400
You're right.

560
00:39:29.560 --> 00:39:31.000
Matty?

561
00:39:36.960 --> 00:39:38.696
Matty. are you there?

562
00:39:38.720 --> 00:39:41.400
Matty. we're police officers.
We want to talk to you.

563
00:39:47.280 --> 00:39:50.200
I'll grab the branch.
Stand there in case he legs it.

564
00:40:13.040 --> 00:40:14.960
PHONE RINGS

565
00:40:18.000 --> 00:40:22.096
-Any progress?
-You'll be the first to know. sir.

566
00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:24.096
I don't need to tell you
it would make everyone's life

567
00:40:24.120 --> 00:40:26.376
considerably easier if we could
wrap this thing up quickly.

568
00:40:26.400 --> 00:40:29.800
Absolutely. sir -
you don't need to tell me that.

569
00:40:31.520 --> 00:40:35.056
A young woman is dead.
The prime suspect's missing.

570
00:40:35.080 --> 00:40:38.416
Social media's rife with speculation
and anti-Traveller sentiment.

571
00:40:38.440 --> 00:40:41.136
and you're leading a team which is.
to put it mildly. operating

572
00:40:41.160 --> 00:40:44.216
under a cloud. I hardly think
this is the time for insolence.

573
00:40:44.240 --> 00:40:46.680
Detective Chief Inspector. Do you?

574
00:40:47.640 --> 00:40:49.480
No. sir.

575
00:40:52.440 --> 00:40:54.360
PHONE VIBRATES

576
00:40:56.880 --> 00:40:59.240
Please tell me
you've found Matty Gough.

577
00:41:00.480 --> 00:41:02.680
POLICE RADIO CHATTER

578
00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:15.496
He was stabbed?

579
00:41:15.520 --> 00:41:19.136
One stab wound. Significant
blood loss on the clothing.

580
00:41:19.160 --> 00:41:22.656
-Hardly any on the ground.
-Well. so he wasn't killed here.

581
00:41:22.680 --> 00:41:25.736
Someone who knew this was
a good place to hide a body.

582
00:41:25.760 --> 00:41:28.176
Traces of blood suggest
they set him down there

583
00:41:28.200 --> 00:41:29.760
to clear a path into the den.

584
00:41:30.720 --> 00:41:32.976
Well. it feels like someone
familiar with these woods. then.

585
00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:36.536
Well. Gifford reckons anyone
who grew up locally hung out here.

586
00:41:36.560 --> 00:41:39.976
-No murder weapon?
-We're looking for a blade. Puncture wound.

587
00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:42.256
PHONE VIBRATES

588
00:41:42.280 --> 00:41:45.856
-Sorry. one second.
-There's nothing on the time of death yet.

589
00:41:45.880 --> 00:41:49.136
but if you want an educated guess.
I'd say close to Lisa's.

590
00:41:49.160 --> 00:41:52.856
-But no idea whether it was before or after?
-No. not yet.

591
00:41:52.880 --> 00:41:55.256
So Matty was last seen
with a bag over his shoulder.

592
00:41:55.280 --> 00:41:58.176
-It's gone. Phone. too.
-Seriously?

593
00:41:58.200 --> 00:42:00.976
Well. we now know it wasn't him
who turned the phone on an hour ago.

594
00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:03.896
-so that's something.
-Nichols is worried things are turning nasty

595
00:42:03.920 --> 00:42:07.496
-at the Travellers site.
-Right. I'll take over the crime scene.

596
00:42:07.520 --> 00:42:09.976
-you two better get down there.
-Really? Are you sure. boss?

597
00:42:10.000 --> 00:42:12.216
-I think maybe we shou...
-Yes.

598
00:42:12.240 --> 00:42:15.936
And I don't appreciate
my instructions being questioned.

599
00:42:15.960 --> 00:42:17.800
Ma'am.

600
00:42:24.960 --> 00:42:26.576
She seem OK to you?

601
00:42:26.600 --> 00:42:29.200
Oh. yeah. she seems 100% Mac to me.

602
00:42:32.720 --> 00:42:35.576
We'll do it my way. OK?
Boys. let's go.

603
00:42:35.600 --> 00:42:37.656
We've got our own way
of doing things. Nichols.

604
00:42:37.680 --> 00:42:40.160
This is one of them.
all right? It's fine.

605
00:42:41.720 --> 00:42:43.120
You see this?

606
00:42:44.080 --> 00:42:47.000
Intimidation. pure and simple.

607
00:42:48.200 --> 00:42:50.656
We're standing up
for one of our own.

608
00:42:50.680 --> 00:42:53.896
A young lassie is dead.
and one of yours did it.

609
00:42:53.920 --> 00:42:56.560
-You shut your mouth!
-You make me. scumbag.

610
00:42:58.520 --> 00:42:59.977
SHOUTING

611
00:43:00.001 --> 00:43:01.480
Hey. hey. hey!

612
00:43:02.400 --> 00:43:05.696
Pack it in! You. home.

613
00:43:05.720 --> 00:43:08.576
-Stay there.
-Might've known you'd stick up for him. eh?

614
00:43:08.600 --> 00:43:10.696
Well. he's already home. isn't he?

615
00:43:10.720 --> 00:43:12.936
Now go on. And you can
take your mates with you.

616
00:43:12.960 --> 00:43:14.440
or I'll nick the lot of you.

617
00:43:15.400 --> 00:43:19.920
-Are you going to behave yourself. big man?
-I'm cool. - Good. Move!

618
00:43:21.000 --> 00:43:23.880
-Thanks. guys.
-All part of the service.

619
00:43:24.840 --> 00:43:29.120
-What's happening?
-Could you just... give us a minute? Thanks.

620
00:43:30.160 --> 00:43:31.616
Coming?

621
00:43:31.640 --> 00:43:33.360
I can't do it. Bart.

622
00:43:34.800 --> 00:43:36.200
OK.

623
00:43:43.640 --> 00:43:45.376
No...

624
00:43:45.400 --> 00:43:47.160
DR IN A WAILS

625
00:43:45.400 --> 00:43:47.136
No!

626
00:43:47.160 --> 00:43:49.176
I'm so sorry. Drina.

627
00:43:49.200 --> 00:43:52.200
No. no. no. no!

628
00:43:54.880 --> 00:43:57.776
-Come on.
-No...

629
00:43:57.800 --> 00:43:59.800
DR IN A WAILS AND SOBS

630
00:44:09.680 --> 00:44:13.016
Right. so how specific can we get
on the time of death?

631
00:44:13.040 --> 00:44:15.456
Exact same two-hour window as Lisa.

632
00:44:15.480 --> 00:44:18.056
So no idea of knowing
who died first?

633
00:44:18.080 --> 00:44:21.736
It's even possible
that someone saw Matty kill Lisa

634
00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:23.656
and then went for him in revenge.

635
00:44:23.680 --> 00:44:26.936
-What have we got on the murder weapon?
-The depth of the wounds

636
00:44:26.960 --> 00:44:29.896
and the damage to the victim's
clothing suggest an unusual blade.

637
00:44:29.920 --> 00:44:32.216
-What. like a hunter's knife?
-Shorter.

638
00:44:32.240 --> 00:44:35.136
More of a dagger. Distinctive.
which could prove helpful.

639
00:44:35.160 --> 00:44:38.536
-Only if we can get our hands on it.
-Matty's phone and bag are missing.

640
00:44:38.560 --> 00:44:40.816
Why risk taking something
that ties you to the victim?

641
00:44:40.840 --> 00:44:42.896
It has to contain
something incriminating.

642
00:44:42.920 --> 00:44:45.576
Well. agreed. but. again.
we havenae got it. All we've got is

643
00:44:45.600 --> 00:44:47.920
two dead teenagers.

644
00:44:50.160 --> 00:44:53.816
Let's hope the search team can find
something at the Travellers site.

645
00:44:53.840 --> 00:44:56.416
Er. Monty. where are we on the DNA?

646
00:44:56.440 --> 00:45:00.296
Well. the party's causing problems.
There was hugging and dancing.

647
00:45:00.320 --> 00:45:04.096
lots of physical contact.
multiple samples on both victims.

648
00:45:04.120 --> 00:45:07.760
The only match our DNA database
spat out was this chap.

649
00:45:10.480 --> 00:45:12.616
No way.

650
00:45:12.640 --> 00:45:13.976
What. do you know him?

651
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:16.800
We just stopped him
beating up Lisa's stepfather.

652
00:45:37.480 --> 00:45:38.816
Nice.

653
00:45:38.840 --> 00:45:41.840
Mm. delightful.

654
00:45:50.240 --> 00:45:52.896
Good work. boys.
Same time Tuesday. OK?

655
00:45:52.920 --> 00:45:57.136
-Mr McIlroy. - Right.
-Hey. Noah. - Hey.

656
00:45:57.160 --> 00:45:59.736
In you go. mate. Do five minutes
on the bike if you're up to it.

657
00:45:59.760 --> 00:46:01.760
-All right?
-OK.

658
00:46:03.160 --> 00:46:05.816
We looked for you at home first.
but your neighbour said

659
00:46:05.840 --> 00:46:07.696
-that you'd be here.
-And here I am.

660
00:46:07.720 --> 00:46:11.496
-Seems like a funny time to be working out.
-The boys need me here.

661
00:46:11.520 --> 00:46:15.296
I run a class a couple of nights
a week. locals and Traveller lads.

662
00:46:15.320 --> 00:46:18.496
I'd rather they work out their
aggression here than on each other.

663
00:46:18.520 --> 00:46:22.096
And when you say "lads".
what age do you mean?

664
00:46:22.120 --> 00:46:23.496
Over-16s.

665
00:46:23.520 --> 00:46:28.056
Oh. right. meaning you're not
subject to a criminal record check

666
00:46:28.080 --> 00:46:31.176
and don't need to declare
your conviction for GBH.

667
00:46:31.200 --> 00:46:35.136
My conviction was downgraded
on appeal. sentence reduced.

668
00:46:35.160 --> 00:46:38.096
Don't suppose that shows up
on your computer. though. eh?

669
00:46:38.120 --> 00:46:42.816
-Apparently not.
-See. I remember. because I represented myself.

670
00:46:42.840 --> 00:46:45.376
So I'm happy to talk if it helps
find out what happened to Matty

671
00:46:45.400 --> 00:46:48.856
and Lisa. But just keep in mind
you're no' dealing with a mug.

672
00:46:48.880 --> 00:46:52.440
-Did Matty ever come to your classes?
-Aye. he was a regular.

673
00:46:53.640 --> 00:46:57.056
Where were you between the hours of
10pm and midnight on Sunday night?

674
00:46:57.080 --> 00:46:59.816
-Direct. I'll give you that.
-Well. two young people are dead.

675
00:46:59.840 --> 00:47:02.456
so there's no sense
in being any other way.

676
00:47:02.480 --> 00:47:04.856
The party started winding down.

677
00:47:04.880 --> 00:47:07.616
After that. I came home
and crashed out.

678
00:47:07.640 --> 00:47:10.536
I'd had a couple of beers.
so I was asleep in no time.

679
00:47:10.560 --> 00:47:12.376
Do you live alone?

680
00:47:12.400 --> 00:47:14.160
-I do.
-Hmm.

681
00:47:17.600 --> 00:47:20.760
If that's all.
I'm getting on now. OK?

682
00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:52.200
PANTING

683
00:47:57.720 --> 00:48:00.360
SHOUTING

684
00:48:12.000 --> 00:48:15.376
There's no obvious motive
for Jackson to kill Matty.

685
00:48:15.400 --> 00:48:18.896
Or Lisa. They were at the party.
but there's no real connection.

686
00:48:18.920 --> 00:48:20.217
KNOCK ON DOOR

687
00:48:20.241 --> 00:48:21.560
Yeah?

688
00:48:23.440 --> 00:48:25.216
Er. if you'll excuse us. guys...

689
00:48:25.240 --> 00:48:28.336
-Actually. it's DI Bartlett I'm after.
-Sir?

690
00:48:28.360 --> 00:48:31.736
-I'll be talking to the media shortly.
-YOU will?

691
00:48:31.760 --> 00:48:35.376
The communications team feel a more
senior officer might be appropriate.

692
00:48:35.400 --> 00:48:40.376
given the developments in the case
and the escalating online tensions.

693
00:48:40.400 --> 00:48:42.376
If you feel like
you're across everything.

694
00:48:42.400 --> 00:48:45.120
Well. I will be once DI Bartlett
brings me up to speed.

695
00:48:47.880 --> 00:48:50.040
Off you go. then. Inspector.

696
00:48:57.560 --> 00:49:01.200
Right. we know Matty was not killed
where his body was found.

697
00:49:02.160 --> 00:49:04.376
I mean. Jackson is
a young. healthy guy. I think

698
00:49:04.400 --> 00:49:06.736
he's more than capable of
carrying a body through the woods.

699
00:49:06.760 --> 00:49:10.096
Mm. How far. though? And if he was
doing some kind of fireman's lift.

700
00:49:10.120 --> 00:49:13.176
-he would have got covered in blood.
-Mm.

701
00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:14.800
LAPTOP CHIMES

702
00:49:19.600 --> 00:49:20.577
KNOCK ON DOOR

703
00:49:20.601 --> 00:49:21.577
Ugh. what now?

704
00:49:21.601 --> 00:49:24.336
Matty's phone was live again. boss.
20 minutes ago.

705
00:49:24.360 --> 00:49:26.160
right in the centre of town.

706
00:49:42.960 --> 00:49:44.960
Did anyone see you come in?

707
00:49:46.320 --> 00:49:50.776
What if they did? I'm just
comforting a friend. aren't I?

708
00:49:50.800 --> 00:49:52.160
Yeah.

709
00:50:06.280 --> 00:50:07.880
It's OK.

710
00:50:12.480 --> 00:50:15.960
If I start. I'll never stop.

711
00:50:19.600 --> 00:50:21.456
ROSE: - Matty?

712
00:50:21.480 --> 00:50:23.016
Matty!

713
00:50:23.040 --> 00:50:26.216
Ohhh. she's been
shouting that for hours.

714
00:50:26.240 --> 00:50:28.600
I don't even think she knows
which Matty.

715
00:50:32.840 --> 00:50:34.560
Drina...

716
00:50:35.520 --> 00:50:37.896
love...

717
00:50:37.920 --> 00:50:40.056
I've done something stupid.

718
00:50:40.080 --> 00:50:41.240
What?

719
00:50:43.600 --> 00:50:45.480
I lied to the police.

720
00:51:13.160 --> 00:51:14.640
Thank you.

721
00:51:17.280 --> 00:51:20.296
It was full to capacity
half an hour ago. 400 vehicles.

722
00:51:20.320 --> 00:51:22.816
most of which leave
when the shops and offices close.

723
00:51:22.840 --> 00:51:26.256
-And the phone was switched on when?
-5.17. for 90 seconds.

724
00:51:26.280 --> 00:51:30.256
-90 seconds... Any CCTV?
-Yes. but the files are corrupted.

725
00:51:30.280 --> 00:51:33.256
Ugh. this is a smart individual.

726
00:51:33.280 --> 00:51:35.576
They needed to access the phone.
for some reason.

727
00:51:35.600 --> 00:51:39.016
so they did it hiding in plain sight
to minimise risk.

728
00:51:39.040 --> 00:51:44.256
Minimise but not eliminate.
I think it's a mistake.

729
00:51:44.280 --> 00:51:46.456
taking the victim's phone.
and they keep turning it on.

730
00:51:46.480 --> 00:51:50.856
It's like they're trying to get rid
of something incriminating.

731
00:51:50.880 --> 00:51:53.480
Like the motive
for a double homicide.

732
00:51:57.880 --> 00:52:00.360
What's this. the Farrar Clinic?

733
00:52:01.320 --> 00:52:03.560
It's a cancer treatment centre.

734
00:52:04.520 --> 00:52:06.296
Why?

735
00:52:06.320 --> 00:52:09.160
Nothing. Sounds familiar.
but nothing.

736
00:52:16.680 --> 00:52:20.936
OK. I want to talk timelines.
So. you spoke to Jackson

737
00:52:20.960 --> 00:52:25.696
-late afternoon at the gym. yeah?
-Yes. -Could it be that he was there

738
00:52:25.720 --> 00:52:29.936
and then in town to activate
Matty's phone at 5.17?

739
00:52:29.960 --> 00:52:32.256
Yeah. just about.

740
00:52:32.280 --> 00:52:34.936
-Have we got something more concrete on him?
-Monty?

741
00:52:34.960 --> 00:52:37.776
We're still getting footage
from Rose's party.

742
00:52:37.800 --> 00:52:41.176
Er. Gemma from the cafe
made the cake. so she filmed this.

743
00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:45.456
So. that's Matty there in the
light jacket. with the yellow bag.

744
00:52:45.480 --> 00:52:48.256
And then here. look.
just zoom in there.

745
00:52:48.280 --> 00:52:52.336
So this guy here. here with
the dark hair. that's Jackson.

746
00:52:52.360 --> 00:52:56.160
-threatening Matty. yeah? - Yep.
-Mm-hm. - I want you to bring him in.

747
00:52:58.600 --> 00:53:01.656
DCI MacMillan? If you're ready
for your interview. we're all set.

748
00:53:01.680 --> 00:53:03.936
Could you just
give us a sec. please?

749
00:53:03.960 --> 00:53:07.896
-I'm just doing my job. DI Bartlett.
-She's right.

750
00:53:07.920 --> 00:53:10.416
You two go and do yours. On you go.
down to the Travellers site.

751
00:53:10.440 --> 00:53:12.656
Oh. actually. I don't think
they'll be there.

752
00:53:12.680 --> 00:53:15.680
They'll all be in the woods.
saying their farewells to Matty.

753
00:53:21.120 --> 00:53:22.720
SHE EXHALES

754
00:53:31.000 --> 00:53:34.456
The Lord is close
to the broken-hearted

755
00:53:34.480 --> 00:53:38.040
and saves those
who are crushed in spirit.

756
00:53:40.000 --> 00:53:47.856
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Believe in God now more than ever.

757
00:53:47.880 --> 00:53:50.696
and trust that in heaven.

758
00:53:50.720 --> 00:53:55.680
you will once again be reunited
with Matty in eternal life.

759
00:53:56.640 --> 00:53:59.000
-Amen.
-ALL: Amen.

760
00:54:00.560 --> 00:54:03.096
I should go check on Rose.

761
00:54:03.120 --> 00:54:05.176
Yeah.

762
00:54:05.200 --> 00:54:06.520
I'll go.

763
00:54:07.480 --> 00:54:10.256
Like. I don't mind.

764
00:54:10.280 --> 00:54:12.240
Thanks. Noah.

765
00:54:17.520 --> 00:54:19.760
He's a good kid you've got there.

766
00:54:20.800 --> 00:54:22.400
Thanks.

767
00:54:43.520 --> 00:54:47.040
Interview commencing
with DCI Cora MacMillan.

768
00:55:00.440 --> 00:55:02.200
DOG BARKS

769
00:55:49.520 --> 00:55:53.856
-This is our tradition.
-First you search our homes. and now this?

770
00:55:53.880 --> 00:55:56.616
Can't you leave us in peace
to pay our respects?

771
00:55:56.640 --> 00:55:59.496
No better way to show our respects
to Matty

772
00:55:59.520 --> 00:56:03.096
-than to find who took his life.
-Yeah. I'm sure a Traveller boy

773
00:56:03.120 --> 00:56:06.096
-is your top priority.
-These guys have been very fair. Jackson.

774
00:56:06.120 --> 00:56:08.656
They said he killed Lisa
until he turned up dead himself.

775
00:56:08.680 --> 00:56:12.136
-Can you keep your voice down. please?
-Not easy when my blood's up.

776
00:56:12.160 --> 00:56:15.000
What about with Matty?
Was your blood ever up with him?

777
00:56:16.520 --> 00:56:20.056
-What's that supposed to mean?
-Did you fight with him at Rose's party?

778
00:56:20.080 --> 00:56:21.960
Yes. about me.

779
00:56:22.920 --> 00:56:26.440
Jackson and me are together.
He was with me that night.

780
00:56:28.120 --> 00:56:30.176
Matty thought it was
too soon after his dad.

781
00:56:30.200 --> 00:56:32.536
and I hoped he would
come around in time.

782
00:56:32.560 --> 00:56:34.096
Fire! Fire!

783
00:56:34.120 --> 00:56:36.360
The caravan! It's Rose.

784
00:56:45.960 --> 00:56:48.456
-Fire Services are on their way.
-We can't wait!

785
00:56:48.480 --> 00:56:51.080
She'll be dead by the time
they get here.

786
00:56:53.200 --> 00:56:55.040
Noah! No. no. no. no!

787
00:56:56.000 --> 00:57:00.216
-Rose! -Lindo!
-Rose!

788
00:57:00.240 --> 00:57:01.817
HE CRIES OUT

789
00:57:01.841 --> 00:57:03.416
Do not go inside that van!

790
00:57:03.440 --> 00:57:07.720
Stand down. That is an order!
Get away from that door!

791
00:57:08.680 --> 00:57:10.536
Rose!

792
00:57:10.560 --> 00:57:12.296
HE COUGHS

793
00:57:12.320 --> 00:57:13.800
Lindo!

794
00:57:16.800 --> 00:57:18.920
Lindo!

795
00:57:26.560 --> 00:57:28.440
Lindo!
